item.title: Fear Hides Your Abundance with Jacqueline Wales
item.description: In this episode, Jacqueline Wales shares her personal journey of living in fear and how it shaped her life. From a dysfunctional family background to battling self-sabotaging behaviors, fear was the driving force behind it all. Jacqueline explores the power of fear, the stories we tell ourselves, and how fear impacts our success. She delves into the concept of abundance, emphasizing the importance of self-awareness and understanding one's own narrative... Feed: https://feeds.captivate.fm/the-abundance-journey/

item.title: "Ad Astra Per Aspera" (SNW S2E2)
item.description: It’s time for a courtroom drama—and the career and life of Una hang in the balance! We discuss Star Trek courtroom dramas, how modern Trek undermines the utopian vision of Gene Roddenberry and makes something even better out of it, and then we enter a Spoiler Closet that’s not particularly spoilery but does involve us trying to make sense of Star Trek economics....
